2026-04-18 — Fix unreadable text in red danger badges (Build page)
===================================================================

Context:
  The red "danger" badges (e.g. "Not found", "Not configured") in the
  Build / Digital Twin and Validation pages used bg-danger bg-opacity-10
  with text-danger — dark red text on a nearly-transparent red background
  — making the text hard to read.

Changes:

1. ``src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js`` — _badge() danger variant:
   replaced ``bg-danger bg-opacity-10 text-danger`` with
   ``bg-danger text-white`` for solid red background with white text.
2. ``src/front/static/domain/js/domain-validation.js`` — _dtBadge()
   danger variant: same change.

